title: Chicago Blackhawks players supporting the Cubs over the years [PHOTOS]
text:
Start Slideshow Â» Patrick Kane, Patrick Sharp, Duncan Keith and Jonathan Toews sing "Take Me Out To The Ballgame" with the Stanley Cup.
Chicago Blackhawks announcer Pat Foley throws out the first pitch at a Chicago Cubs game.
Kane's form looks decent as he delivers his first pitch. He's definitely smoother on the ice, though.
The Chicago Blackhawks have been very successful in recent years and with the Chicago Cubs finding their own success, their paths might be crossing even more in the future.
Chicago Bears players supporting the Cubs over the years [PHOTOS] Above, take a look at many of the Blackhawks players that have come out in support of the Cubs at Wrigley Field as you ready for game three of the National League Division Series between the Cubs and St. Louis Cardinals this afternoon.
